race.comment: It's been more than a year since LOMAX (1) won a race but he gets his chance back to this grade. He's been mixing his form in stronger metropolitan races this campaign but his best is clearly good enough to win this. He maps to get the right run and, provided the track is allowing horses off the speed to blend into the race, he can win. BY THE BOOK (7) went close in a similar grade of race last time. He is drawn alongside LOMAX so it could become a tactical battle. He looks the main danger. OBI (3) is unbeaten in three runs at this track so clearly enjoys racing here. He can mix his form these days so perhaps he is a better place bet. PUNCHIN (6) looks a likely improver second-up and deserves some each-way consideration.
